It’s that time of the year where families come together and celebrate the holidays. 

It’s also a time of the year when many people throughout the world are alone. 

As an ambassador for suicide prevention, I want to take this time to tell everyone who follows me to check on your strong friends. 

Some Facts: 

*Males in the United States are more likely to take their own life at nearly four times the rate of females 

* Male deaths represent 79% of suicides, amounting to roughly 105 men who die by suicide every day.

* USA: Suicide is the 2nd most common cause of death for men under the age of 45.

* Almost 800,000 people die due to suicide every year, nearly twice the number who die by homicide.

1-800-273-TALK (8255) 

You are not alone, asking for help is sign of strength not weakness. Like any disease, depression shows signs and symptoms. Suicide fits no stereotype, people have waves of depression, and I know a lot of people cover it up their pain. 

#worldsuicidepreventionday #depressionhelp #depresion #sucideawareness #mentalillness #love #smile #saythankyou

Big Mirror Big Dreams

My only competition is sitting in the mirror…

Eventually the inevitable will happen. 

I know the value of self-awareness and awareness and they are both so undervalued. 

I have study behavior for the last 10 years. 

Please note that what we are near can be a choice like people, places and things. 

A little insight these choices will dictate who you will become. Choose wisely.

If you work for a douche monkey, sooner or later you’ll become one yourself.

If your colleagues are selfish, sooner or later you become selfish. 

If you hang around someone who’s unkind, you’ll slowly become unkind. 

Little by little, you adopt the thoughts and feelings, the attitudes and standards of the people around you. 

The changes are too gradual to notice until they’re too large to address.

We’ve become a society that uses are thumbs to scroll through photos on a free app to compare ourselves to people we don’t know. 

Make a choice to be kind to one another and always remember we should post the things that make us feel good about ourselves.

PRIDE IS A KILLER…

Realizing our mistakes is key to rectification and betterment, but our pride would never allow us to admit our mistakes.

If you want people to respect you, start by respecting them.

Showing Up vs Present

People who Show Up
1. Want to win. 
2. They have a positive attitude
3. They don't speak for others.

People who are “Present”

Showing up consistently makes you an asset. Simply being present makes you a liability.

Happy Holidays…

NFLPA New York / New Jersey Former Players Chapter celebrates our last event of the year with gratitude. 

I want to acknowledge our sponsor @bernsteinpwm Thank you for your insight and expertise on building wealth. 

Thank you to our keynote speaker @kaplanmobray You are one of a kind and you knock it out of the park every time. ❤️🙏🏽

Thank you to our venue @northjerseycc and its amazing menu and incredible staff. 

Big ups to my brother @dereckfaulkner You have delivered time and time again. You are everything a chapter president should be. 

It has been an emotional year for a lot of us, when we reflect and look around we are all dealing with something. 

We should all take these last 27 days of the 2023 to reflect on the positives and the relationships we have forged. 

For me, my mother has been dealing with multiple health issues after suffering her second stroke in March. She has been resilient and continues to get better each day. 

My father had a knee replacement two weeks ago and he seems to be locked in and looking forward to rehab. He is a soldier- he’ll be alright 👍🏽 

The one thing we all can reflect on is how we behaved in 2023. Knowing that behavior is a choice not a skill. 

What I know is owning your mistakes, showing that you have learned and evolved, will almost always get you a second chance. 

Remember not to believe those who tell you they love you. Believe those who show you they do.

Let’s all be thankful and bring 2023 home on a good note, and remember we are all just passing through! 

Sean L. James

Who we are is defined by what we do, not what we say. 

While our words are how we see ourself, our actions are how other people see us.

Why your smallest interactions are actually your biggest. 

Being kind can quite literally change the trajectory of your life.

Being un-kind is a tax on your talent - it will weigh down your potential.

None of us imperfect human beings are going to be able to achieve perfect kindness at all times. 

The secret to life is that there is no secret. Actions are what separate people from who they are and who they want to be.

Wherever there is a human being, there is an opportunity for kindness.

Thank you 🙏🏽❤️ Usain Bolt @usainbolt

TRUST…

It’s the glue to humanity! 

Its presence cements relationships by allowing people to live and work together, feel safe and belong to something bigger then themselves. 

When we have Trust- It makes us want to be part of a team, relationship, or group with a shared purpose and a willingness to depend on each other. 

When we trust we are willingly to contribute what is needed, not just by offering our selves, but also by sharing our heart, talent, energy and honest thoughts on how the relationship or group is working and how we can evolve. 

When don’t have Trust- We withdraw our energy and level of engagement. 

We will pull back from that person or relationship and no longer feel part of their world. 

This loss of trust can be obvious or somewhat hidden especially if we pretend to be present but inwardly disengage. Basically we just don’t fuck with you anymore! 

I write about these things because they’re important to me. I’ve been on both sides of trust..

I’ve been trusted and I’ve not been trusted...and believe me it’s a horrible feeling not to be trusted by something or someone you care about. 

My intentions will always be to make people feel safe. When people feel safe they will give you all they can. 

They will flourish...more importantly when we feel safe we become better humans. 

 #trust #gamechanger #humanbehavior #gothaveit #love #smile #saythankyou
